OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHarvard president sorry for
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fremarks on antisemitism    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Harvard's president has apologised for 
OL,6, controversial remarks she made at a    
OL,7, congressional hearing about            
OL,8, antisemitism on US college campuses.   
OL,10,FWhen asked whether calls for the       
OL,11,Fgenocide of Jews constituted harassment
OL,12,Funder university policy, Dr Claudine   
OL,13,FGay said it depended on the context.   
OL,15,FDr Gay, and two other university       
OL,16,Fpresidents who gave similar answers,   
OL,17,Fhave since faced fierce criticism.     
OL,19,F"I am sorry," she said in an interview 
OL,20,Fwith The Crimson student newspaper.    
